CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Flash Newspicture Magazine, January 3, 1938, p. 16, reads: "Pittsburg's [Pittsburgh's] Floyd Britton paused just a moment between his daily program of much activity. The Business of being one of the town's most popular, as well as one of the most energetic and enterprising young contact men, keeps gentleman Floyd quite busy.  If it's journalism, athletics or salesmanship, see Floyd."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Floyd Britton posed with foot on running board of car with "Flash" sign in window, parked in front of church
